(563, 112, 1, 1288, 4, '1 : Conductive primer \n- APPG was almost 100% supplier at VPPL - I for all shades and they raised price for conductive primer from Rs 228/- per litre to Rs 270/- per liter with average consumption of 7 to 7.5 KL per month giving impact of Rs.3.0 lacks per month.\n- modified and re-establish the conductive primer from KNPL to reduce the additional cost burdan of Rs 3.0 Lacks pm from Sept 12 onward. Recurring saving will be about Rs 3.0 Lac / month.\n- APPG finally reduce the price to Rs 255/- per lit but as a strategy we kept them away .\n- As an alternative source developed and tried out as a standbye source DuPont and Nippon Paint. DuPont paint results are quite OK.\nAlso tried out water base conductive primer from Nippon Paints. However had some application issues.\n2. Musturd Yellow shade with improved opacity\nPoor opacity ( 50 microns )  of Mustured yellow  base pose problem of higher consumption  ( 450 ml/set ) and productivity loss due to speed loss . Alternative shade developed got approved through BAL Styling and Engg Dept and modified sample tried out with optimum workability.( opacity coverage 25 - 30 microns , consumption 260 ml/set ) \nConsumption optimisation gave  saving about Rs 100/- per set. \n- In order to improve the productivity  2 Coat - 1 bake M Yellow shade developed .so as to take up on automation .. However since the volume of Pulsar 200 NS did not pick up as expected , and existing paint stock and RM with KNPL can suffice over 6 months requirement , implementation delayed.\n- Opacity issue with Tosca Red was also optimised with Asian PPG.\n\n3. Go Green Initiative  : Bio Degradable sludge pit chemicals which improves sludge pit water quality and  discardal frequency. Also anticipates sludge volume generation due to bio degradation  , by about 20% reducing the cost of sludge disposal. The system is implemented in June 13 with the existing bath with old chemicals and results will be seen in next 2-3 months. Approximate saving per month is about Rs 1.0 Lacs per month.\n- Combined Degreasing cum plastic conditioning chemical to reduce no of stages from 5 to 3 and the effluent generation as well as reduce LPG consumption. Initial problem of water not getting dry was resolved with chemical modification. System is running fine. However customer has taken objection on the implementation without their approval. Samples submitted for all the long term testing at BAL . Results awaited.\nSaving potential about Rs.1.5 + Lacs/month.apart from Go Green Initiative.\n- Supported Corp Materials team by co-ordination with KNPL to get 1.5 % Discount on the sale value . Sale for Apr 2012-  Mar 2013 is about 6.0 crore. ', 136, '2013-07-03 07:03:58'),
(564, 112, 1, 1289, 4, 'Evaluated VPPL- I , VEPL- PN and Badve Engg Paint shop in terms of \na) No of vehicle set plastic parts supplied per month to BAL respective branch. Showing productivity trend as Badve >>> VEPL PN >> VPPL - I paint shop.\nb) When compared with No of parts supplied per month more or less trend is same as above.but the quantum reduced.\nc) However when the surface area of the components supplied per month is compared all three suppliers VPPL- I . VEPL - PN and Badve Engg almost equal .\n- This has reduce confusion that Badve Engg supplying 1,60,000 veh set per month , VEPL- PN about 120,000 Veh set per month and VPPL- I supplies only 70,000 - 80,000 plastic part vehicle sets to BAL - respective plant.\n\n', 136, '2013-07-03 07:03:58'),
(565, 112, 1, 1290, 4, '- Poor opacity ( 50 microns )  of Mustured yellow base pose problem of higher consumption  ( 450 ml/set ) and productivity loss due to speed loss . Alternative shade developed got approved through BAL Styling and Engg Dept and modified sample tried out with optimum workability.( opacity coverage 25 - 30 microns , consumption 260 ml/set ) \nConsumption optimisation gave  saving about Rs 100/- per set. \n- In order to improve the productivity  2 Coat - 1 bake M Yellow shade developed .so as to take up on automation .. However since the volume of Pulsar 200 NS did not pick up as expected , and existing paint stock and RM with KNPL can suffice over 6 months requirement , implementation delayed.\n- Opacity issue with Tosca Red was also optimised with Asian PPG.\n- Adhesion failure issue of top coat on satin black ( Dual tone finish on tank side cover ) was resolved , by adjusting formulation and the surface hardness of Satin black shade.\n- VA/VE proposal was given for the matt polishing on the plastic part instead of satin black paint , however it was not accepted by BAL for the reason - abrasion resistance with denim cloth is poor.\n', 136, '2013-07-03 07:03:58'),
(566, 112, 1, 1291, 4, '- Closed all the RFQs raised from TDC as well as Marketing team for customers BAL,VW,Eischer Volvo,M&M ,Royal Enfield etc including the BOM.', 136, '2013-07-03 07:03:58'),
(567, 112, 1, 1292, 4, '- New technology feasibility study tried out for following.\n1. Dry Ice ( CO2 ) Cleaning of plastic parts in place of acquous pre-treatment . Good saving potential is there along with the Green process reducing the environmental impact. The initial investment is high , however pay back period is < 3 Months. \n\n2. Tried out single coat UV Curable paint on PP substrate especially for the BOLERO Cladding . The system works out ok only with the chlorinated PP primer for effective adhesion. Single coat UV curable coating for ABS is successful. \n- BIo degradable sludge pit additives to improve the sludge pit water quality and about 20 % reduction in sludge genearation . Approx Saving per month is about Rs 1.0 Lacks , chemicals implemented from May 2013 , we will get the results from 2 - 3 months after implementation. \n- Identified use of water base carbon nano tube emulsion to make plastic part conductive to eliminate the use of conductive primer prior to electrostatic painting . Feasibility is seen , however the carbon nano tubes in India is very less. Can be imported and tried out wtth some paint manufacturer / resin manufcaturer. Work will be further taken up with M/s Aerofine polymers, Grauer and Weil to see the workability. This involves investment in CNT to a tune of about Rs 4 - 5 Lacks.', 136, '2013-07-03 07:03:58'),
(568, 112, 1, 1293, 3, '1. - VPPL BN small paint shop : Plant commissioned and plant ready for trials by 30th June , 2013 ,though the customer commitment is July 15 , 2013. \n\n- Based on the customer requirement , defined the plant design criteria, layout with available space , getting quote from various supplier ,finally gone ahead with Taikisha. Involved in detailed plant layout and design reviews and  finalisation , monitored project installation schedule and removed the bottlenecks ( Fan fabrications with ABBOT , and diverted part orders on Nadi ) so as to meet the commissioning target of June 30 , 2013.\nThough on phone coordinated with Taikisha , conv supplier and plant , could not visit to VPPL- BN for progress review from Mid May to June 3rd week due to operation . However close check on progress was ensured.\n- VPPL- I plant capacity and future BAL volume projection studied and worked out for low budget ( Rs . 1.6 Cr )small paint shop requirement to cater about 1,50,000 small comp/month. \nkeeping the capacity flexibility.\nAlso worked out small booth with conv oven to cater requirement of about 35,000 comp /month .\nHowever could not persue my self effectively for the choice due to budget constraint. \n', 136, '2013-07-03 07:03:58'),
